Command from Image
REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE
ON employees
FROM 'employee_user';
Simple Meaning

Remove UPDATE and DELETE permissions from the user.

User can no longer:

❌ Modify data
❌ Delete data

But still may have:

✅ SELECT permission

Real Example
REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE
ON students
FROM 'student1'@'localhost';
Before REVOKE
User	Permissions
student1	SELECT, UPDATE, DELETE
After REVOKE
User	Permissions
student1	SELECT only
Example Table
students table
student_id	name
1	Arun
2	Ravi
Before REVOKE

User student1 can run:

UPDATE students
SET name = 'Kumar'
WHERE student_id = 1;

and

DELETE FROM students
WHERE student_id = 2;
After REVOKE

If user tries UPDATE:

UPDATE students
SET name = 'Kumar'
WHERE student_id = 1;
Result
ERROR:
Permission denied

=======

Easy Understanding

| Command | Meaning          |
| ------- | ---------------- |
| GRANT   | Give powers      |
| REVOKE  | Take back powers |


==========

Admin → GRANT → User gets access

Admin → REVOKE → User loses access

